        MODULE-2:-RESET
=============================================================
The VPN reset process identifies the peer IP from the crypto
map configuration and terminates the active session using

'vpn-sessiondb logoff tunnel-group <peer-ip>'.

The tunnel status is verified using
    'show crypto ikev1 sa'
    and
    'show crypto ipsec sa'.
===========================================================
STEP 1 - CHECK EXISTING VPN STATUS
-----------------------------------------------------------
Command:show crypto ikev1 sa
Purpose:Check Phase-1 (IKE) Security Associations.
If a peer IP is present → Phase-1 tunnel is active.

Command:show crypto ipsec sa
Purpose:Check Phase-2 (IPsec) Security Associations.
If the peer IP appears → IPsec tunnel is passing traffic.
-----------------------------------------------------------
STEP 2 - IDENTIFY VPN CONFIGURATION
-----------------------------------------------------------
Command:show run crypto map
Purpose:Used to read the VPN crypto map configuration.
Extracts:
- Crypto map name
- Sequence number
- Peer IP address
This information is used to identify the correct VPN tunnel
that needs to be reset.
-----------------------------------------------------------
STEP 3 - RESET / TERMINATE VPN SESSION
-----------------------------------------------------------
Command:vpn-sessiondb logoff tunnel-group <peer-ip>
Example:vpn-sessiondb logoff tunnel-group 4.227.229.249
Purpose:Terminates the existing VPN session associated with the
specified tunnel-group (peer IP).
Effect:
- Clears the active VPN session
- Forces the tunnel to renegotiate when traffic starts again
-----------------------------------------------------------
STEP 4 - POST RESET VERIFICATION
-----------------------------------------------------------
Command:
show crypto ikev1 sa
show crypto ipsec sa
Purpose:
Verify that the existing VPN sessions have been cleared.
