CISCO ASA VPN AUTOMATION – REAL PRODUCTION WORKFLOW

This module handles VPN configuration updates on Cisco ASA.

Workflow Overview:

1.  Netmiko establishes SSH connection to ASA Firewall to read the current configuration and apply

from netmiko import ConnectHandler   #  from Netmiko library we aare importing ConnectHandler class
connect_handler = ConnectHandler(
    device_type="cisco_asa", #(Syntax:parameter=value)
    host="159.66.72.50",, #(Syntax:parameter=value)
    username="admin",, #(Syntax:parameter=value)
    password="password", #(Syntax:parameter=value)
)

2. Disable Pagination

   -Command: terminal pager 0 #To disable pagination

   -Cisco ASA normally pauses long command outputs with "--More--".
    Automation requires full command output without interruption,
    so pagination is disabled.

3. Verify VPN Peer Exists
   Syntax:show run tunnel-group <peer_ip>
   Command:show run tunnel-group 4.227.229.249


4. Identify Crypto Map to check current VPN configuration
   Command:show run crypto map

    The crypto map defines the core VPN configuration including:
    • Crypto map name
    • Sequence number
    • Peer IP
    • Transform set
    • Encryption domain ACL

5. Identify Encryption Domain
-An encryption domain defines which local and remote networks are allowed
 to communicate through the IPsec VPN tunnel.

-Command:show run access-list <acl_name>
-Example:show run access-list outside_cryptomap_1
-Output:
access-list outside_cryptomap_1 extended permit ip
192.168.10.0 255.255.255.0
10.2.5.0 255.255.255.0


6. Parse Object Networks:- To Extract real subnet from object network
-Command:show run

Command
--------------------------------------------------
show run  (to find IP and subnet mask for object network)
--------------------------------------------------
Syntax
--------------------------------------------------
object network <object_name>
 subnet <ip_address> <subnet_mask>

Example Output
--------------------------------------------------
object network 10.2.5.0_24
 subnet 10.2.5.0 255.255.255.0

object network 10.2.6.0_24
 subnet 10.2.6.0 255.255.255.0

How Automation Extracts It
--------------------------------------------------
The automation runs "show run" and reads the output
line-by-line. When it finds the keyword "object network",
it stores the object name. When it finds the "subnet"
line below it, it extracts the IP and subnet mask.

Code with Comment
--------------------------------------------------
show_run = connection.send_command("show run")


objects = {} # dictionary to store object → subnet mapping

current_object = None

for line in show_run.splitlines():

    # detect object network
    if line.startswith("object network"):
        current_object = line.split()[2]

    # detect subnet inside object
    elif line.strip().startswith("subnet") and current_object:

        parts = line.strip().split()

        ip = parts[1]       # subnet IP
        mask = parts[2]     # subnet mask

        objects[current_object] = (ip, mask)

        current_object = None



